  "beats": [
    {
      "zh": "明明半小时就能写完的东西，你却拖到了凌晨。",
      "scene": "S1-01",
      "en": "Something you could finish in half an hour, you put off until the dead of night.",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-01.mp3",
      "audioStart": 0,
      "audioEnd": 5120
    },
    {
      "zh": "不是你不会做，而是一直在等一个「更好的状态」。",
      "scene": "S1-01",
      "en": "It's not that you can't do it — you're waiting for a 'better mood' that never comes.",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-01.mp3",
      "audioStart": 5120,
      "audioEnd": 10841
    },
    {
      "zh": "同事小林，把方案拖到交付当天才动笔，",
      "scene": "S1-02",
      "en": "A colleague put off the proposal until the day it was due,",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-02.mp3",
      "audioStart": 0,
      "audioEnd": 4400
    },
    {
      "zh": "通宵赶工，还是漏掉了客户最在意的那一条。",
      "scene": "S1-02",
      "en": "pulled an all-nighter, and still missed the one point the client cared about most.",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-02.mp3",
      "audioStart": 4400,
      "audioEnd": 8960
    },
    {
      "zh": "一笔谈了半年的长期合作，几十万的单子，就这样飞了。",
      "scene": "S1-02",
      "en": "Six months of talks, a six-figure deal — gone, just like that.",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-02.mp3",
      "audioStart": 8960,
      "audioEnd": 13793
    },
    {
      "zh": "体检单上写着「建议复查」，你想着「过阵子再说」，",
      "scene": "S1-03",
      "en": "The check-up form said 'follow-up advised,' and you thought 'later,'",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-03.mp3",
      "audioStart": 0,
      "audioEnd": 5120
    },
    {
      "zh": "一拖就是半年。有些事，拖掉的不只是时间。",
      "scene": "S1-03",
      "en": "and half a year slipped by. Some things, delaying them costs more than time.",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-03.mp3",
      "audioStart": 5120,
      "audioEnd": 9796
    },
    {
      "zh": "但先别急着责怪自己。",
      "scene": "S1-04",
      "en": "But don't be so quick to blame yourself.",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-04.mp3",
      "audioStart": 0,
      "audioEnd": 2880
    },
    {
      "zh": "心理学家早就说过：拖延，根本不是时间管理的问题，",
      "scene": "S1-04",
      "en": "Psychologists said it long ago: procrastination isn't about time management,",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-04.mp3",
      "audioStart": 2880,
      "audioEnd": 7520
    },
    {
      "zh": "而是情绪管理的问题。",
      "scene": "S1-04",
      "en": "it's an emotion-management one.",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-04.mp3",
      "audioStart": 7520,
      "audioEnd": 9718
    },
    {
      "zh": "研究者西罗斯与皮切尔指出：",
      "scene": "S1-05",
      "en": "Researchers Sirois and Pychyl point out:",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-05.mp3",
      "audioStart": 0,
      "audioEnd": 2960
    },
    {
      "zh": "拖延，是用逃避眼前的坏情绪，去换未来更大的麻烦。",
      "scene": "S1-05",
      "en": "procrastination trades away one bad feeling now for far bigger trouble later.",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-05.mp3",
      "audioStart": 2960,
      "audioEnd": 8046
    },
    {
      "zh": "去给大脑做个扫描你会看到，一想到讨厌的任务，",
      "scene": "S1-06",
      "en": "Scan the brain and you'll see: the moment we picture a dreaded task,",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-06.mp3",
      "audioStart": 0,
      "audioEnd": 4640
    },
    {
      "zh": "大脑里处理「疼痛」的区域，就会真的亮起来。",
      "scene": "S1-06",
      "en": "the regions that handle 'pain' genuinely light up.",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-06.mp3",
      "audioStart": 4640,
      "audioEnd": 9360
    },
    {
      "zh": "拖延，其实是大脑在本能地「躲开疼」。",
      "scene": "S1-06",
      "en": "Procrastination is really the brain instinctively dodging pain.",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-06.mp3",
      "audioStart": 9360,
      "audioEnd": 13244
    },
    {
      "zh": "更麻烦的是「现时偏误」：",
      "scene": "S1-07",
      "en": "Worse still is what's called 'present bias':",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-07.mp3",
      "audioStart": 0,
      "audioEnd": 4000
    },
    {
      "zh": "我们总是高估眼前的舒服，低估未来的代价。",
      "scene": "S1-07",
      "en": "we keep overrating today's comfort and underrating tomorrow's cost.",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-07.mp3",
      "audioStart": 4000,
      "audioEnd": 7967
    },
    {
      "zh": "那怎么办？第一招：只先做五分钟。",
      "scene": "S1-08",
      "en": "So what do we do? Tip one: just start for five minutes.",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-08.mp3",
      "audioStart": 0,
      "audioEnd": 3200
    },
    {
      "zh": "不求做完——",
      "scene": "S1-08",
      "en": "Not to finish it —",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-08.mp3",
      "audioStart": 3200,
      "audioEnd": 3920
    },
    {
      "zh": "只求开始。先动起来，状态自己会跟上。",
      "scene": "S1-08",
      "en": "just to begin. Once you're moving, the mood catches up on its own.",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-08.mp3",
      "audioStart": 3920,
      "audioEnd": 7706
    },
    {
      "zh": "比如写报告，别再对着空白文档干耗。",
      "scene": "S1-09",
      "en": "Take writing a report — stop staring at the blank page.",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-09.mp3",
      "audioStart": 0,
      "audioEnd": 3840
    },
    {
      "zh": "打开豆包，跟它说一句「帮我搭个报告框架」，",
      "scene": "S1-09",
      "en": "Open Doubao and just say, 'draft me a report outline,'",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-09.mp3",
      "audioStart": 3840,
      "audioEnd": 9600
    },
    {
      "zh": "AI 时代，比起做到完美，更重要的是让想法先落地。",
      "scene": "S1-09",
      "en": "In the age of AI, getting the idea moving matters more than getting it perfect.",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-09.mp3",
      "audioStart": 9600,
      "audioEnd": 15151
    },
    {
      "zh": "第二招：给拖延装一个开关——番茄钟。",
      "scene": "S1-10",
      "en": "Tip two: give procrastination an off-switch — the Pomodoro timer.",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-10.mp3",
      "audioStart": 0,
      "audioEnd": 6240
    },
    {
      "zh": "定个 25 分钟的闹钟，这段时间里只做这一件事，",
      "scene": "S1-10",
      "en": "Set a 25-minute alarm, and for those minutes do this one thing only,",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-10.mp3",
      "audioStart": 6240,
      "audioEnd": 10800
    },
    {
      "zh": "把手机翻面、放到够不着的地方，铃一响，就奖励自己歇会儿。",
      "scene": "S1-10",
      "en": "flip your phone face-down, out of reach; when it rings, take a break.",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-10.mp3",
      "audioStart": 10800,
      "audioEnd": 18991
    },
    {
      "zh": "别为已经拖掉的时间懊恼——自责只会喂大焦虑，焦虑又会喂大拖延。",
      "scene": "S1-11",
      "en": "Don't dwell on lost time — blame feeds anxiety, and anxiety feeds delay.",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-11.mp3",
      "audioStart": 0,
      "audioEnd": 6400
    },
    {
      "zh": "执行力不是天赋，是一次次「先开始」攒出来的。",
      "scene": "S1-11",
      "en": "Drive isn't a gift — it's built up from starting, again and again.",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-11.mp3",
      "audioStart": 6400,
      "audioEnd": 10320
    },
    {
      "zh": "你不必等到准备好，现在，就动一下。<END>",
      "scene": "S1-11",
      "en": "You don't have to wait until you're ready. Right now — just make one move.",
      "audioFile": "audio/scene-S1-11.mp3",
      "audioStart": 10320,
      "audioEnd": 13949
    }
  ],
